# .trivyignore — accepted-risk suppressions for Trivy SCA
#
# Trivy auto-discovers this file at the repo root; no caller change needed.
#
# RULES (enforced in review):
#   1. Never add a bare CVE ID. Every entry MUST have, on the comment lines above it:
#        - reason (no fix available, or path unreachable/not exploitable)
#        - owner (@github-handle)
#        - tracking ticket (SEC-xxx)
#        - re-evaluation / expiry date
#   2. If a fix exists and the upgrade is feasible — upgrade the dependency instead.
#   3. For long-term accepted risk prefer .trivyignore.yaml (supports `expires`).
#
# Full guide: https://github.com/tava-health/infra-github-actions/blob/main/docs/trivy-sca.md
#
# (No active suppressions yet.)
